st: the lessons
r: The Celebrant may introduce the Scripture readings in these or similar words
tb: Let us hear the record of God’s saving deeds in history,
    remembering how he saved his people in ages past and in the
    fullness of time sent his Son to be our Redeemer; and let us pray
    that God may bring to completion in each of us the saving work
    he has begun.
r: At least three of the following Lessons are read, of which one is always the Lesson
    from Exodus. After each Lesson, the Psalm or Canticle listed, or some other
    suitable psalm, canticle, or hymn, may be said or sung. A period of silence may be
    kept; and the Collect provided, or some other suitable Collect, may be said.
